    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-02-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-02-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="594" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d594">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Douglass</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-02-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 13,
                            1891</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 97.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 120, of the 26th
                        ultimo, replying to my No. 89, of the 9th ultimo, and reporting the result
                        of your conferences with Mr. Firmin on the inconveniences caused to American
                        commerce by the Haitian law requiring the detention of vessels in Haitian
                        ports until the import duties on their cargoes are paid by the
                        consignees.</p>
                <p>You will continue to keep the matter in view. Messrs. Brett, Son &amp; Co.,
                        of New York, have been informed of your efforts to remedy the evil
                        complained of.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James G. Blaine</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
